column1: Metadata
These are the data from the Drosophila selection experiment published in:
Scheiner SM Caplan RL and Lyman RF. 1989. A search for trade-offs among life history traits in Drosophila melanogaster. Evolutionary Ecology 3:51-63.
See Materials and Methods section for details.
Funding: NIH R01-GM38201
Data columns (each line consists of one F1 female)
Col 1 = Sire
Col 2 = Dam
Col 3 = Rearing temperature (19C or 25C)
Col 4 = Thorax length (mm)
Col 5 = Age at death (days)
Col 6 = Age at peak fecundity (days)
Col 7 = Peak fecundity (number of eggs)
Col 8 = Fecundity during last third of adult life span (number of eggs laid)
Col 9 = Total number of eggs laid
Col 10 = Number of eggs laid on days 5-7
Col 11 = Number of eggs laid on days 8-10
Col 12 = Number of eggs laid on days 11-13
Col 13 = Number of eggs laid on days 14-16
Col 14 = Number of eggs laid on days 17-19
Col 15 = Number of eggs laid on days 20-22
Col 16 = Number of eggs laid on days 23-25
Col 17 = Number of eggs laid on days 26-28
Col 18 = Number of eggs laid on days 29-31
Col 19 = Number of eggs laid on days 32-34
